<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>Creating a Lexer Project File</title>
    <link href="../../style/style.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" />
</head>
<body>
    <h1>
        1.2.6 Creating a Lexer Project File
    </h1>

    <p>
        A lexer project file consists of references to token, keyword, expression and lexer files.
    </p>

    <p>
        The lexer project file syntax is described in <a href="../../syntax/lexer.html#project-file-syntax">this</a> document.
    </p>

    <p>
        To add a lexer project file to minilang:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>
            Right-click your project in the Solution Explorer and select 'Add | New Item...'.
        </li>
        <li>
            Select Visual C++ | Utility | Text File (.txt) item and name the file <span class="mono">minilang.slg</span>.
        </li>
        <li>
            Add the following code to the lexer project file:<br />
			<ref file="ref/minilang.slg.div"/>
        </li>
    </ul>
</body>
</html>
